The paper deals with medical image segmentation using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses multi-task learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of ground truth segmentation maps and feature maps also suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the experiments conducted in the paper involve the evaluation of different architectures, which could be related to neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
